<OPENER><DATELINE><HI>At a Meeting of the</HI> MARINE SOCIETY <HI>in</HI> SALEM, <DATE><HI>March</HI> 31, 1791.</DATE></DATELINE></OPENER>
<P>VOTED,</P>
<P>THAT Captain JONATHAN MASON, &s;enior, and General FISK, be a Committee to wait upon the Rev. Mr. BENTLEY, with the thanks of the SOCIETY for his SERMON on the death of JONATHAN GARDNER, ESQUIRE, and to reque&s;t a copy for the pre&s;s.</P>
